ed descriptions of image content and associate them with images this work will change the paradigm of medical imaging instead of clinical systems storing just pixels they will store image data plus the image meaning this will enable a broad range of computational analytic functionality including semantic search see iq project integration of image and non image data statistical modeling of disease and intelligent decision support applications for image based personalized care related people mark a musen md ph d professor of medicine biomedical informatics division head bmir co director biomedical informatics training program daniel l rubin md ms assistant professor of radiology and of medicine bmir related publications bmir 2009 1389 the cabig annotation and image markup project ds channin p mongkolwat v kleper ks supekar dl rubin journal of digial imaging march published in 2009 bmir 2008 1315 medical imaging on the semantic web annotation and image markup dl rubin p mongkolwat v kleper ks supekar ds channin aaai spring symposium series semantic scientific knowledge integration stanford published in 2008 related events special colloquium cabig imaging face to face meeting date tue sep 9 2008 to wed sep 10 2008 time 12pm location stanford university project annotation and image markup aim project go stanford biomedical infomatics only all of stanford school of medicine contact information maps & information site map stanford university
